node.text:
New account as old one was hacked

Who am I ‚Ä¶ ?

My name is Mackenzie or just Mac, I live in the Scottish Highlands where I make props for TV & Film.

I have always had an interest in making things ever since I watched Alien & Labyrinth Sadly my art teacher thought there was no future for me in making props as ‚Äúit wasn‚Äôt real art‚Äù

When I was in my last year at school I was hit by a drunk driver who mounted the curb as I walked home from school After spending 3 months in ICU I then had to learn to walk again (Aug 22 I can now walk for about 5-6 minutes, mostly around my place but still use a chair for anything longer) This also gave me the opportunity to indulge in my passion of mixing films with making props and set me on my path to my current career

I now make props & sets for film & TV with a bit of storyboarding & conceptual design added to the mix I am classed as a Generalist in the industry or Jack of all trades to you and me

I started out in TV working on shows for the BBC & Netflix then moved to Pinewoods working on large scale film productions I work a lot on location around the world on films Now I work exclusively for one director As most of my work is under NDA (means I cannot share) this account will be just for personal projects to share with you

I now work in pre production on the east coast of USA mostly Atlanta but also other various locations Being in a chair does not inhibit me. I use an off road chair for hiking & camping Race my friends roller blading Love Mountain biking & swimming/diving Only thing that holds me back is peoples subconscious prejudice that having a disability makes you less human or worthy for them 

Most of all I just want to share my artwork hoping you will like the stuff I make 

NFS = Not For Sale

Mac

node.text:
People only want me for my connections üòú

Last month @doctinfoil (Warren Beaton) found some unseen footage of a birthday skit he and Russell Crowe @russellcrowe  made for Ron Howard's birthday Warren asked me to get Russell's permission and I was able to help connect the two later that evening to release it publicly. It was so much fun sorting out and it went viral. My original video was viewed hundred of thousands of times within 48 hours and it was picked up by various news channels & outlets 

(accidently deleted the original post on IG so reposting to keep for posterity)

#russellcrowe #warrenbeaton #paltiya #weta #ronhoward #birthday #sfx #sfxmakeup #sfxartist #sfxgore #viralvideos #viral

Cannae wait for this - See you there! 

On September 23rd, join authors¬†Howard Berger¬†@hoops511 and¬†Marshall Julius @vintagegeekcentral¬†at¬†@the_montalban ¬†in Hollywood as they pick the brains of a panel of film and television's greatest Masters of Make-Up Effects, presented by¬†Nostalgic Nebula. Hear the stories from the artists and take a deep dive into the history behind some of the most iconic creatures, appliances and make-up effects seen on screen. 

Following the show will be a signing of Masters of Make-Up Effects: A Century of Practical Magic with Howard Berger, Marshall Julius and panel members including @tamilynnlane , @mikeyrots, Leonard Engelman, @prenticemargaret, @jkelmakeup , @kruegermekash, Stephen Prouty, @bcorso , Greg Nelson, and @haney7560.

Tickets at www.nostalgicnebula.com (LINK IN BIO)

node.text:
"At the end of the day, filmmaking is a team, but eventually there's got to be a captain" ‚Äì Sir Ridley Scott

On this day I was just finishing working at Pinewood studios on the film ‚ÄúLuther‚Äù starring Idris Elba and about to start working with the Russo brothers on a film called The Grey Man and saw this gentleman who was walking to his car Approaching him nervously I asked him if he had any positions available as he should hire me because I was passionate about film making & good at what I did He laughed at my cheekiness and got into his car We parted, wishing each other to have a great day A week later I had an email inviting me to an interview as he had checked out my work I was hired later that day as part of his permanent crew 
NEVER WASTE AN OPPORTUNITY 
IT COULD CHANGE YOUR LIFE

Art credit: Julian Rentzsch

Spending next week knocking together an art room in my friends spare room as I flit between Atlanta & Massachusetts Dusting off all the prep I have been doing for so many projects including this one as I will have a functioning place instead of hotel beds and benches while doing pre production on film projects

#captainamerica #avengers #thefirstavengers #americasass #steverogers #3dprinting @3dassemble #russobrothers #chrisevans @therussobrothers @chrisevans
